author: TimesReporter.com staff report
title: Area college note: Shutt finishes off fall at YSU
text: Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 11:49 PM By TimesReporter.com staff report Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 11:49 PM Courtney Shutt (Dover) fired a 237 (80-74-83) as the Youngstown State womenâ€™s golf team concluded a strong fall campaign with a seventh-place finish at the MAC Fall Preview recently at Purgatory Golf Club in Noblesville, Indiana. YSU carded a three-round total of 927 for the event which was won by Toledo. The Penguins, Indiana State, UIC and Cleveland State were the only non-MAC teams in the 13-team field. YSU finished ahead of MAC schools Ohio, Bowling Green and Central Michigan at the tournament. This was the final fall tournament for the Penguins, who will return to action Feb. 6-7 when they face Cleveland State in Orlando. By TimesReporter.com staff report
